behavior cook_chicken(chicken:item, stove:item, fryingpan:item):
    body:
        assert is_food_chicken(chicken)
        assert is_stove(stove)
        assert is_fryingpan(fryingpan)
        achieve inside(fryingpan, stove)
        achieve on(chicken, fryingpan)
        achieve is_on(stove)

behavior boil_pasta(pasta:item, pot:item, stove:item):
    body:
        assert is_dry_pasta(pasta)
        assert is_pot(pot)
        assert is_stove(stove)
        achieve inside(pasta, pot)
        achieve inside(pot, stove)
        achieve is_on(stove)

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        bind chicken: item where:
            is_food_chicken(chicken)
        
        bind stove: item where:
            is_stove(stove)
        
        bind fryingpan: item where:
            is_fryingpan(fryingpan)
        
        cook_chicken(chicken, stove, fryingpan)

        bind pasta: item where:
            is_dry_pasta(pasta)
        
        bind pot: item where:
            is_pot(pot)
        
        boil_pasta(pasta, pot, stove)

def has_pasta_and_chicken_combined(pasta: item, chicken: item):
    # Determine whether pasta and chicken are combined
    symbol combined=exists fryingpan: item: is_fryingpan(fryingpan) and on(pasta, fryingpan) and on(
chicken, fryingpan)
    return combined

behavior combine_pasta_and_chicken(pasta: item, chicken: item):
    body:
        bind fryingpan: item where:
            is_fryingpan(fryingpan)
        # Locate the fryingpan
        achieve on(pasta, fryingpan) and on(chicken, fryingpan)
        # Combine the pasta and chicken in the fryingpan

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        bind pasta: item where:
            is_dry_pasta(pasta)
        # Bind the pasta
        bind chicken: item where:
            is_food_chicken(chicken)
        # Bind the chicken
        if not has_pasta_and_chicken_combined(pasta, chicken):
            combine_pasta_and_chicken(pasta, chicken)
        # Ensure that the pasta and chicken are combined if not already done

def chicken_and_pasta_combined(fryingpan:item, pot:item, stove:item):
    # Function to check if chicken and pasta are in the same container
    symbol are_combined=exists o: item : (is_food_chicken(o) and inside(o, fryingpan) and inside(pot
, stove))
    return are_combined

behavior combine_chicken_and_pasta(chicken:item, pasta:item, pot:item, fryingpan:item, stove:item):
    body:
        achieve inside(chicken, fryingpan) # Ensure chicken is in the fryingpan
        achieve inside(pasta, pot)        # Ensure pasta is in the pot
        achieve inside(pot, stove)        # Ensure pot is stove
        
        # Ensure the stove is on to facilitate mixing
        achieve is_on(stove)  
        
        # If chicken and pasta are not in the same container, ensure they are
        if not chicken_and_pasta_combined(fryingpan, pot, stove):
            achieve inside(chicken, pot)
        
        achieve is_off(stove) # Turn off the stove for safety

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        bind chicken: item where:
            is_food_chicken(chicken)
        bind pasta: item where:
            is_dry_pasta(pasta)
        bind pot: item where:
            is_pot(pot)
        bind fryingpan: item where:
            is_fryingpan(fryingpan)
        bind stove: item where:
            is_stove(stove)
        
        combine_chicken_and_pasta(chicken, pasta, pot, fryingpan, stove)

def has_cooked_chicken_and_pasta(stove:item):
    # Function to check if there are cooked chicken and pasta on the stove
    symbol has_chicken_and_pasta=exists x: item : (is_food_chicken(x) or is_dry_pasta(x)) and on(x, 
stove)
    return has_chicken_and_pasta

behavior combine_chicken_and_pasta(chicken:item, pasta:item, plate:item):
    body:
        achieve inside(chicken, plate)
        achieve inside(pasta, plate)

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        bind stove: item where:
            is_stove(stove)
            # Select the stove
        if has_cooked_chicken_and_pasta(stove):
            # If both chicken and pasta are cooked and on the stove, proceed

                is_food_chicken(cooked_chicken) and on(cooked_chicken, stove)
            # Select the cooked chicken on the stove
            bind cooked_pasta: item where:
                is_dry_pasta(cooked_pasta) and on(cooked_pasta, stove)
            # Select the cooked pasta on the stove
            bind plate: item where:

            # Select a plate for combining
            combine_chicken_and_pasta(cooked_chicken, cooked_pasta, plate)

            # Observing if the items are not present
            foreach stove:item:
                if is_stove(stove) and not visited(stove):
                    observe(stove, "Check if there is cooked chicken and pasta on the stove")
